<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,651,1218]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,651,678]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
“Corallum irregularly sympodially branched but not pinnulate; branching multidirectional or flabellate. Branchlets arranged irregularly, loosely bilateral or uniserial, usually bent to some degree. Spines small, simple with smooth surface; triangular, conical or blister-shaped, often poorly developed or absent on older parts of the corallum. Polyps with 12 mesenteries; round with well-developed tentacles, arranged in a single row at terminal branchelets. Adjacent polyps often unequal” (
<bibRefCitation author="Molodtsova, T. N." box="[661,871,796,822]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="52 - 64" refId="ref48095" refString="Molodtsova, T. N. (2011) A new species of Leiopathes (Anthozoa: Antipatharia) from the Great Meteor seamount (North Atlantic). Zootaxa, 3138 (1), 52 - 64. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3138.1.3" type="journal article" year="2011">Molodtsova, 2011</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,651,1218]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,832,858]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Remarks.</emphasis>
Phylogenetic studies (using mtIGRs, CO3-CO1, and nuclear sequences 18S and 28S), match with well-defined diagnostic features, pointing to the monophyly of the monogeneric Family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haeckel" authorityYear="1896" box="[1151,1300,868,894]" class="Anthozoa" family="Leiopathidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="family">Leiopathidae</taxonomicName>
, which may require the establishment of a higher taxonomic status (
<bibRefCitation author="Brugler, M. R. &amp; Opresko, D. M. &amp; France, S. C." box="[774,998,904,931]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="312 - 361" refId="ref46567" refString="Brugler, M. R., Opresko, D. M. &amp; France, S. C. (2013) The evolutionary history of the order Antipatharia (Cnidaria: Anthozoa: Hexacorallia) as inferred from mitochondrial and nuclear DNA: implications for black coral taxonomy and systematics. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 169 (2), 312 - 361. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / zoj. 12060" type="journal article" year="2013">
Brugler 
<emphasis box="[868,918,904,930]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">et al</emphasis>
., 2013
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Wagner, D. &amp; Opresko, D. M." box="[1009,1302,903,931]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="277 - 289" refId="ref50406" refString="Wagner, D. &amp; Opresko, D. M. (2015) Description of a new species of Leiopathes (Antipatharia: Leiopathidae) from the Hawaiian Islands. Zootaxa, 3974 (2), 277 - 289. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3974.2.11" type="journal article" year="2015">Wagner &amp; Opresko, 2015</bibRefCitation>
). The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haime" authorityYear="1849" box="[151,274,940,966]" class="Anthozoa" family="Leiopathidae" genus="Leiopathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,274,940,966]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Leiopathes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is composed of nine species which have been widely recorded around the globe, at depths ranging from 
<quantity box="[151,303,976,1003]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2185" metricValueMax="2.4" metricValueMin="0.037" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" unit="m" value="1218.5" valueMax="2400.0" valueMin="37.0">37 to 2400 m</quantity>
, but no records for the South Atlantic hitherto. Within the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haime" authorityYear="1849" box="[1031,1154,976,1002]" class="Anthozoa" family="Leiopathidae" genus="Leiopathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1031,1154,976,1002]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Leiopathes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, there are two easily distinguishable forms in terms of branching patterns: sparsely branched forms with long terminal branches [
<taxonomicName authority="(Esper, 1792)" authorityName="Esper" authorityYear="1792" baseAuthorityName="Esper" baseAuthorityYear="1792" class="Anthozoa" family="Antipathidae" genus="Antipathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="glaberrima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">L. glaberrima</emphasis>
(Esper, 1792)
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pax, 1915)" authorityName="Pax" authorityYear="1915" baseAuthorityName="Pax" baseAuthorityYear="1915" box="[374,643,1047,1074]" class="Anthozoa" family="Leiopathidae" genus="Leiopathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="valdiviae">
<emphasis box="[374,506,1048,1074]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">L. valdiviae</emphasis>
(Pax, 1915)
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="Opresko, 1998" authorityName="Opresko" authorityYear="1998" box="[654,1012,1048,1074]" class="Anthozoa" family="Leiopathidae" genus="Leiopathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="acanthophora">
<emphasis box="[654,839,1048,1074]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">L. acanthophora</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Opresko, D. M." box="[845,1012,1048,1074]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="99 - 111" refId="ref48733" refString="Opresko, D. M. (1998) Three new species of Leiopathes (Cnidaria: Anthozoa: Antipatharia) from Southern Australia. Records of the South Australian Museum, 31 (1), 99 - 111." type="journal article" year="1998">Opresko, 1998</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="Opresko, 1998" authorityName="Opresko" authorityYear="1998" box="[1022,1299,1048,1074]" class="Anthozoa" family="Leiopathidae" genus="Leiopathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="bullosa">
<emphasis box="[1022,1132,1048,1074]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">L. bullosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Opresko, D. M." box="[1139,1299,1048,1074]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="99 - 111" refId="ref48733" refString="Opresko, D. M. (1998) Three new species of Leiopathes (Cnidaria: Anthozoa: Antipatharia) from Southern Australia. Records of the South Australian Museum, 31 (1), 99 - 111." type="journal article" year="1998">Opresko,1998</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="Molodtsova, 2011" authorityName="Molodtsova" authorityYear="2011" class="Anthozoa" family="Leiopathidae" genus="Leiopathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis box="[1310,1436,1049,1074]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">L. montana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Molodtsova, T. N." box="[151,357,1084,1110]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="52 - 64" refId="ref48095" refString="Molodtsova, T. N. (2011) A new species of Leiopathes (Anthozoa: Antipatharia) from the Great Meteor seamount (North Atlantic). Zootaxa, 3138 (1), 52 - 64. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3138.1.3" type="journal article" year="2011">Molodtsova, 2011</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; and 
<taxonomicName authority="Wagner &amp; Opresko, 2015" authorityName="Wagner &amp; Opresko" authorityYear="2015" box="[415,820,1083,1111]" class="Anthozoa" family="Leiopathidae" genus="Leiopathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="annosa">
<emphasis box="[415,525,1085,1110]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">L. annosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Wagner, D. &amp; Opresko, D. M." box="[531,820,1083,1111]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="277 - 289" refId="ref50406" refString="Wagner, D. &amp; Opresko, D. M. (2015) Description of a new species of Leiopathes (Antipatharia: Leiopathidae) from the Hawaiian Islands. Zootaxa, 3974 (2), 277 - 289. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3974.2.11" type="journal article" year="2015">Wagner &amp; Opresko, 2015</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
] and forms with short fan-shaped branches (
<taxonomicName authority="Johnson, 1899" authorityName="Johnson" authorityYear="1899" class="Anthozoa" family="Leiopathidae" genus="Leiopathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="expansa">
<emphasis box="[1315,1436,1085,1110]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">L. expansa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Johnson, J. Y." box="[151,316,1120,1146]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="813 - 824" refId="ref47502" refString="Johnson, J. Y. (1899) Notes on the antipatharian corals of Madeira, with descriptions of a new species and a new variety, and remarks on a specimen from the West Indies in the British Museum. Journal of Zoology, 68 (1 - 4), 813 - 824. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1469 - 7998.1899. tb 07913. x" type="journal article" year="1899">Johnson, 1899</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="Roule, 1902" authorityName="Roule" authorityYear="1902" box="[327,607,1120,1146]" class="Anthozoa" family="Leiopathidae" genus="Leiopathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="grimaldii">
<emphasis box="[327,461,1120,1146]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">L. grimaldii</emphasis>
Roule, 1902
</taxonomicName>
; and 
<taxonomicName authority="Opresko, 1998" authorityName="Opresko" authorityYear="1998" box="[666,962,1120,1146]" class="Anthozoa" family="Leiopathidae" genus="Leiopathes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Antipatharia" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="secunda">
<emphasis box="[666,787,1120,1146]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">L. secunda</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Opresko, D. M." box="[794,962,1120,1146]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="99 - 111" refId="ref48733" refString="Opresko, D. M. (1998) Three new species of Leiopathes (Cnidaria: Anthozoa: Antipatharia) from Southern Australia. Records of the South Australian Museum, 31 (1), 99 - 111." type="journal article" year="1998">Opresko, 1998</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
). In the latter group, the terminal branches usually occur on the convex side of larger, fan-shaped branches (
<bibRefCitation author="Molodtsova, T. N." box="[876,1084,1156,1182]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="52 - 64" refId="ref48095" refString="Molodtsova, T. N. (2011) A new species of Leiopathes (Anthozoa: Antipatharia) from the Great Meteor seamount (North Atlantic). Zootaxa, 3138 (1), 52 - 64. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3138.1.3" type="journal article" year="2011">Molodtsova, 2011</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Opresko, D. M." box="[1096,1264,1156,1182]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="99 - 111" refId="ref48733" refString="Opresko, D. M. (1998) Three new species of Leiopathes (Cnidaria: Anthozoa: Antipatharia) from Southern Australia. Records of the South Australian Museum, 31 (1), 99 - 111." type="journal article" year="1998">Opresko, 1998</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
